declarations.comments: `replace word searchValue replaceValue replaceReplacedWords` will match the `word` against `searchValue` and replace matched strings with `replaceValue`.
declarations.title: replace

declarations.comments: `replaceWithFuncSingle word searchValue f replaceReplacedWords` will match the `word` against `searchValue` and replace matched strings with the string resulting from invoking `f`.
declarations.title: replaceWithFuncSingle

declarations.comments:
`replaceWithFuncMultiple word searchValue f replaceReplacedWords` will match the `word` against `searchValue` and replace matched strings with the string resulting from invoking `f`.
The difference between this and `replaceWithFuncSingle` is that the `f` here takes two `String` arguments.
declarations.title: replaceWithFuncMultiple

children.comments: Representing that the source collection of strings has been exhausted.
children.title: eof

children.comments: Representing general parser error. Currently not used.
children.title: parseError

declarations.comments: The `OwoifyError` class represents those types denoting errors when owoifying.
declarations.title: OwoifyError

declarations.comments: `count unconsFunc n p` will replicate owoify parser according to the specified `uncons`, length (`n`) and a collection of owoify functions.
declarations.title: count

declarations.comments: A simple type representing errors that occur during owoification.
declarations.title: OError

declarations.comments: `runOwoifyParser (OwoifyParser f)` simply executes (unwraps) the parser inside the monad.
declarations.title: runOwoifyParser

declarations.comments: Utility function to interleave two lists.
declarations.title: interleave

declarations.comments:
`owoify source level` will owoify source string using the specified level.
Currently three levels are supported, from weak to strong: `Owo`, `Uwu`, `Uvu`
declarations.title: owoify
